\subsubsection{Per-Window Active Labels}
\label{track:window-auto-suspend}

Window auto-suspend has different semantics from pane auto-suspend.
Instead of following terminal focus, it follows whether the tracked tmux
window is selected by any attached client.  To support that, we keep a
window-scoped labels file analogous to the pane labels file.

<<helper functions>>=
def window_labels_path(
    window_id: str, who: str
) -> pathlib.Path:
    """Return path to a tracked window's labels file."""
    safe_window = window_id.replace("@", "window_")
    return (
        get_tracking_dir()
        / f"window_labels_{safe_window}"
        f"_{sanitize_who(who)}.json"
    )
@

We reuse the same absent-versus-empty distinction as for panes:
[[None]] means the window is not tracked, while an empty list means the
tracked file exists but currently has no labels.

<<helper functions>>=
def read_window_labels(
    window_id: str, who: str,
) -> Optional[List[str]]:
    """Read tracked window labels, or ``None`` if absent."""
    path = window_labels_path(window_id, who)
    try:
        return json.loads(path.read_text())
    except (OSError, json.JSONDecodeError):
        return None
@

Writing again uses an atomic temporary file in the same directory.

<<helper functions>>=
def write_window_labels(
    window_id: str, who: str,
    labels: List[str],
) -> None:
    """Atomically write a tracked window's labels."""
    path = window_labels_path(window_id, who)
    path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)
    tmp = path.with_suffix(".tmp")
    tmp.write_text(json.dumps(labels))
    tmp.rename(path)
@

As with panes, we merge new labels while preserving order and skipping
duplicates.

<<helper functions>>=
def add_window_labels(
    window_id: str, who: str,
    labels: List[str],
) -> None:
    """Add labels to a tracked window's active set."""
    existing = read_window_labels(window_id, who) or []
    seen = set(existing)
    merged = list(existing)
    for lbl in labels:
        if lbl not in seen:
            merged.append(lbl)
            seen.add(lbl)
    write_window_labels(window_id, who, merged)
@

Removing labels shrinks the file or deletes it entirely when the last
tracked label disappears.

<<helper functions>>=
def remove_window_labels(
    window_id: str, who: str,
    labels: List[str],
) -> None:
    """Remove labels from a tracked window's active set."""
    existing = read_window_labels(window_id, who)
    if existing is None:
        return
    to_remove = set(labels)
    remaining = [
        lbl for lbl in existing
        if lbl not in to_remove
    ]
    if remaining:
        write_window_labels(window_id, who, remaining)
    else:
        delete_window_labels(window_id, who)
