\subsubsection{Shell Command Builders}

Building the shell commands that tmux hooks execute follows the
same pattern as [[build_detached_track_finalize_command]]: set
[[PYTHONPATH]], invoke the hidden CLI command, and pass the relevant
tmux identifier ([[pane_id]] or [[session_id]]) plus worker identity
when needed.

<<helper functions>>=
def build_detached_nytid_prefix() -> str:
    """Return the PYTHONPATH and Python prefix for detached commands."""
    pythonpath = os.path.abspath(
        os.path.join(
            os.path.dirname(__file__),
            "..", "..", "..",
        )
    )
    return (
        f"PYTHONPATH={shlex.quote(pythonpath)} "
        f"{shlex.quote(sys.executable)} "
        "-c 'from nytid.cli.track import cli;"
        " cli()'"
    )
@

The pane suspend command no longer receives labels as arguments---it
reads them from the pane's active labels file (see above).  It only
needs the pane ID (to locate the file) and the worker identity.

<<helper functions>>=
def build_detached_suspend_command(
    who: str,
    pane_id: str,
) -> str:
    """Return shell command to suspend tracking on focus-out."""
    prefix = build_detached_nytid_prefix()
    cmd = (
        f"{prefix} "
        f"_suspend-detached"
        f" --pane-id {shlex.quote(pane_id)}"
    )
    if who != default_username:
        cmd += f" --who {shlex.quote(who)}"
    return cmd
@

Window auto-suspend uses one hidden dispatcher command keyed by
[[session_id]] rather than one hidden command per [[window_id]].  The
dispatcher scans tracked windows for all workers, so one worker's tmux
launch cannot overwrite another worker's hooks in the same session.  It
queries tmux at hook time so detach/reattach and multiple attached
clients are handled from current tmux state without accumulating stale
per-window hook entries.

<<helper functions>>=
def build_detached_window_sync_command(
    session_id: str,
) -> str:
    """Return shell command to synchronize tracked windows in a session."""
    prefix = build_detached_nytid_prefix()
    cmd = (
        f"{prefix} "
        f"_sync-window-tracking-detached"
        f" --session-id {shlex.quote(session_id)}"
    )
    return cmd
@

The pane resume command is simpler: it reads labels from the state file
written during suspend, so it needs the pane ID and only passes worker
identity when it differs from the default.

<<helper functions>>=
def build_detached_resume_command(
    who: str,
    pane_id: str,
) -> str:
    """Return shell command to resume tracking on focus-in."""
    prefix = build_detached_nytid_prefix()
    cmd = (
        f"{prefix} "
        f"_resume-detached"
        f" --pane-id {shlex.quote(pane_id)}"
    )
    if who != default_username:
        cmd += f" --who {shlex.quote(who)}"
    return cmd
